document_metadata.name: Screening of a neuronal cell model of Tau pathology for therapeutic compounds

citation.name: Neurobiology of aging
citation.title: Screening of a neuronal cell model of tau pathology for therapeutic compounds.

links.evidence: As shown before, Tau aggregation (on the level of oligomeric and/or fibril aggregates) is toxic for cells.

citation.name: Neurobiology of aging
citation.title: Screening of a neuronal cell model of tau pathology for therapeutic compounds.

links.evidence: The dose response screening identified compounds related to the inhibition of 3 major targets led to inhibition of Tau aggregation: p38 MAPK (7 out of 8 compounds in the initial library), VEGFR1/2 (3 of 8) and TGF (3 of 10).

citation.name: Neurobiology of aging
citation.title: Screening of a neuronal cell model of tau pathology for therapeutic compounds.

links.evidence: Tab. 1A-B: Summary of the Tau aggregation modulators (inhibitors = 18 (A), stimulators = 10 (B)) which show decrease / increase in the amount of ThS + cells without affecting the expression level of TauRD∆K compared to the compound untreated control.

citation.name: Neurobiology of aging
citation.title: Screening of a neuronal cell model of tau pathology for therapeutic compounds.

links.evidence: Treatment with Givinostat (1.2 µM) lead to a nearly 7-fold increase in the fraction of ThS + cells (from ~ 12% to ~ 84%, Fig. S4A and B, blue lines) compared to the uninduced control, and 2.5-fold compared to the induced control.
